item.title: Delta, or pi?
item.dc:creator: @the_wanderer The Wanderer
item.description:
@the_wanderer wrote:

Here’s my recommendations.

moparisthebest.com

moparisthebest.com

programming, irc, cars


Great server. Has SQL integrated which gives it a big plus. Just take the extra time to look up how SQL works. It really is a lot easier to read that config files and the like. He also tells you how to set a MySQL server up, and if you need any help just post in here and I’ll help you set one up. Has a decent amount of content. Only bad thing is that it is a delta based server still (although I believe the framework was redone heavily).

Any RuneSource deviation would be great. Reference this image for RuneSource deviations.

2mfac7d.png1183×364

Hyperion’s iServer looked nice, although I believe it didn’t have much content, not 100% sure. Just look at those different possibilities and chose the one you like the best. My favorite out of all of those is RuneSource. I liked Stonefall because it already had SQL integrated, but it didn’t have a lot of content, so you may want to stay away from it for now.

Also, I HIGHLY suggest you actually read some books on Java before you try coding. This will help you out in the long run. A great book I found you can read in my signature. Other alternatives are listed here by Mendorphins (<3 u bebe)

moparisthebest.com

moparisthebest.com

programming, irc, cars

I tried one of those books (Bleeding through the keyboard) and I really didn’t like the teaching style. I found that book that is in my signature on my iPod and I loved it. I have tried reading the tutorials on Oracle and I can’t simply stand them. It’s all about how you prefer being taught, and to me, how it is presented.
